The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Exam vigil by police
                                                                                                               Exam vigil by police
                            
	Calcutta police will take up a slew of measures for Madhyamik 2009, which begins on Wednesday.        
	 Policemen will keep an eye on photocopy centres to check cheating.        
	 Playing loudspeakers has been banned.        
	 Cops will be posted at exam centres.        
	 Additional traffic cops will be deployed to ensure smooth movement of vehicles.         
	 Movement of heavy and medium goods vehicles will be restricted on exam days from 8am to noon.        
	Medical Bank, a voluntary organisation in Sovabazar, will offer medical help to examination centres in north Calcutta if any student falls ill while writing the papers. Medical Bank can be contacted at 9831062157.                                                                                                                                                                           
